snippet.textDisplay: I started watching the NBA here in Italy when you and Penny got into the League. You, Kobe and all these guys have been the people I have grown up watching, you have always been there. Now a huge piece of my teenage times has gone, and seeing you cry like a little baby just hurts even more, it adds pain to pain. It's gonna be tough, just live through it, embrace these feelings, that's the only way you'll be able to deal with them. I have been reflecting on my life these days since that damned Sunday. I am going through hard times myself right now and what happened has made me realize a few things that I hope will help me out, and the same may be for many others. The greatness of people like Kobe passing away lies in the impact they have on people's lives, not only when they're still around. Love you Shaq, much respect to you for pouring it out on TV, showing us all how sensitive and caring of a person you are. Cheers my Big Man
snippet.textOriginal: I started watching the NBA here in Italy when you and Penny got into the League.
